# C4 Level 4: Code Diagram

The Code diagram is the lowest level of detail, showing how a single component is implemented.

## Core Principles (MANDATORY)

- **Optionality:** Level 4 is usually optional. Only use it when the internal implementation is too complex.
- **Specific Implementation:** Use standard UML class diagram notation or ER diagrams.
- **Keep it Focused:** Don't diagram the entire codebase.

## Mermaid Templates

### UML Class Diagram Template
```mermaid
classDiagram
    class User {
        +int id
        +string username
        +save()
    }
    class AuthService {
        +authenticate(username, password)
    }
    AuthService --> User : Uses
```

### ER Diagram (Database) Template
```mermaid
erDiagram
    USER ||--o{ ORDER : places
    USER {
        int id PK
        string username
    }
    ORDER {
        int id PK
        int user_id FK
    }
```
